The Edo State secretariat of the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) has received 1,400 corps members posted to the state for the 2022 Batch ‘B’ Stream II service. The NYSC State Coordinator, Mrs Abiodun Olubukola, disclosed this yesterday in Benin while speaking with journalists. She said the formal opening/swearing in ceremony would take place on July 26. She further said, “In Edo State, the course will take place at the permanent orientation camp in Okada, Ovia North East KGA.” 